{"name": "libmytoken", "metadata": {"name": "libmytoken", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: Information Technology", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "Intended Audience :: System Administrators", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Security", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: System :: Systems Administration :: Authentication/Directory", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": "https://github.com/oidc-mytoken/libpy", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": "https://mytoken-docs.data.kit.edu", "dependencies": [], "summary": "A python library for interacting with a mytoken server.", "upload_time": 1690538208}, "documentation": ["# libmytoken\n\nA python library for interacting with a [mytoken server](https://github.com/oidc-mytoken/server).\n\nThis is the very first alpha version of the library, which currently only supports obtaining OpenID Connect access\ntokens from a mytoken.\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nimport libmytoken\n\nat = libmytoken.get_access_token_from_jwt_mytoken(mytoken)\n\nmytoken_server = libmytoken.MytokenServer(\"https://mytoken.data.kit.edu\")\nat = mytoken_server.AccessToken.get(mytoken)\nfull_response = mytoken_server.AccessToken.api_get(mytoken)\n\n```\n\n### Error Handling\n\nThe library will raise an exception of type `MytokenError` if something goes wrong.\n\nError Handling can be done the following way:\n\n```python\ntry:\n    print(libmytoken.get_access_token_from_jwt_mytoken(mytoken))\nexcept libmytoken.MytokenError as e:\n    print(\"ERROR mytoken: {}\".format(e))\n```\n\n## Installation\n\n`pip install libmytoken`\n\n## License\n\n`libmytoken` is provided under the [MIT License](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT).\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "libmytoken.from_jwt", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "libmytoken.from_jwt.get_access_token_from_jwt_mytoken", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "mytoken", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "scopes", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "audiences", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "comment", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "libmytoken.accesstoken", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "libmytoken.accesstoken.AccessTokenEndpoint", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "libmytoken.accesstoken.AccessTokenEndpoint.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "endpoint", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "libmytoken.accesstoken.AccessTokenEndpoint.api_get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mytoken", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "oidc_issuer", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "scopes", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "audiences", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "comment", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "libmytoken.accesstoken.AccessTokenEndpoint.get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mytoken", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "oidc_issuer", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "scopes", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "audiences", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "comment", "type": null, "default": ".